there was a moment where many pubs tried micropayments. conversion was bad. core readers were more likely to convert on a sub cta. passive readers rarely bothered. best micropayment conversion I saw was about 0.003% of monthly reads

did the research and ran a few tests wasn't promising for pubs with 1-5m monthly reads

in my tests, I found that even a 1/5 of cost recovery per average story production cost using micropayments was highly unlikely

It annoyed readers as another cash ask. It triggered more compliant messages than introducing subs/membership

specific to my test pubs the average lifespan of a story was 3-5 days
